SYMPTOM_TEXT: A few hours after getting my first shot of the Pfizer vaccine, my left arm started to hurt.  It was hard to move without intense muscular pain.   Later that night, I woke up with severe upper back pain.   After taking a Tylenol and putting a heating pad on my back, I tried to go back to sleep but couldn't.  The pain lasted until a little after 5 am.   On the day after my injection, I started to get a fever around noon.  I accidentally broke my thermometer while washing it.  My last reading (around 3 PM) was 100 degrees.  I definitely felt feverish throughout the rest of the day and into the evening.  My muscles throughout my body also felt tired/sore.  My husband said that my forehead was really warm.  Later in the evening (around 7 PM), my legs began to have intense pain.  The muscular pain was centralized behind both thighs and calves.  I put a heated massage pillow against the areas to try to relieve the pain.  It helped for small intervals, but did not cure it.  I also used a heating pad and Tylenol to try to fight the pain.  I also tried to drink lots of water.   At 10:30 PM, the pain was unbearably intense, causing me to have a panic attack (which of course made things worse).  After another Tylenol and session with the heating pad, I was finally able to fall asleep (over an hour later).  I woke up around 3:00 AM drenched in sweat from breaking my fever.   Since breaking my fever, I have had almost no further adverse symptoms (besides my muscles feeling "slightly" sore).  I feel it should be noted that I had COVID-19 twice before getting the vaccine and am considered a "long-hauler."  The first time was last March (2020) and the second time was in October (2020).  With these illnesses, I have had many ill effects.  My hair began thinning a lot, I lost over 30 pounds (now considered underweight), was diagnosed with POTS, struggle with gastrointestinal problems (was put on low-FODMAP diet), and my extreme fatigue never really went away.
OTHER_MEDS: escitalopram oxalate (10 mg; 1/day) busPIRone (10 mg; 2/day) fludrocortisone (2.5 mg; 2/day) midodrine (2.5 mg; 3/day) buPROPion (150 mg; 1/day)
HISTORY: Postural Orthostatic Tachycardia Syndrome Irritable Bowel Syndrome Anxiety
ALLERGIES: Allergies: codeine, penicillin  Intolerant to: lactose, fructans

It was not nearly as bad as the first incident, and by morning the bleeding was again decreasing and by the end of the day my urine was visibly clear. April 2 ? again slight bleeding in the evening and by the next morning the bleeding was again decreasing and by the end of the day my urine was visibly clear. April 3 ? at 3 in the morning (April 4) I had slight bleeding when I got up to go to the bathroom.  Slight bleeding was still present in the morning April 4 but cleared by the end of day.
LAB_DATA: My doctor did not feel the bleeding was connected the Pfizer vaccine, but rather an immune response and since the bleeding stopped each time did not feel any treatment was necessary.

Patient reported:  Difficulty breathing; severe headaches, vomiting/nauseous for 3 weeks and counting, plus chills.  Went to Urgent Care 4.1.21.  Back to Urgent Care 4.9.21 - this time with symptoms above plus cough, SOB, N/V.  CXR (-) COVID (-).  Patient received dose J&J vaccine 3.23.21.  HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS: Patient is a 59 y.o. female who presents to the Urgent Care with COVID-19 (sick after receiving COVID vaccine x1week ago. Vomiting, headaches, nausea, chills)  HPI:  Patient presents today with complaints of nausea, vomiting, headache and chills intermittently over the past 1 week after receiving her 1st COVID 19 vaccination.  She states that she got the Johnson Johnson COVID-19 vaccine.  She states of then she has had an episode of vomiting daily some nausea.  She has also had a headache every single day as well as some constipation.  She denies any numbness or tingling, abdominal pain, diarrhea.  She states that she has been taking ibuprofen, Pepto-Bismol, and Tylenol for her symptoms with minimal relief.  She is drinking a lot of water as well.  Medical Decision Making:  No concerns for acute abdomen or neurological deficits are noted on exam today. Patient is reporting some symptomatic relief after receiving the Toradol injection today in urgent care. Educated the patient on the following: Zofran for nausea and vomiting. MiraLax and senna for any constipation symptoms.  Motrin and Tylenol for pain or fever. Drink plenty of fluids.  Follow up with PCP as needed. If symptoms worsen go to the emergency room such as you are not able to keep fluids down while taking the Zofran, if you develop any bloody stools, bloody vomit, or increasing abdominal pain.  HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS Patient is a 59 y.o. female who presents to the Urgent Care with COUGH (cough, SOB, congestion, vomiting everyday until about 1PM. headache off and on. x 2 weeks (since covid vaccine))     HPI: Patient is a 59 y.o. female who presents to the urgent care with cough, shortness of breath, congestion, nausea and vomiting and intermittent headaches over the past 2 weeks.  Patient states that the symptoms started the day of her COVID vaccine.  She states that she receive the Johnson&Johnson 1 time dose.  She states later that day after receiving the vaccination she had a significant headache that developed.  She states that since then she has had a dry nonproductive cough with intermittent shortness of breath and morning nausea and vomiting that last till about 1:00 p.m..  She states that the headaches have resolved at this time but the cough, intermittent shortness of breath and nausea and vomiting have persisted.  She denies any abdominal pain, chest pain, chest pressure or chest tightness.  She states that she has not been experiencing any dizziness, vision changes or lightheadedness.  She was seen in the urgent care about a week ago and was prescribed Zofran to assist with the nausea.  She states that she was taking it twice in the morning and has now been able to only take it once, does feel that the nausea is improving but was out of the medication today, states that she was not able to take anything today and did have an episode of nonbloody nonbilious vomiting.  She states that she was having some constipation she feels that this was related to the over-the-counter pain medications that she was taking for the headaches.  She states that she was advised to take MiraLax at her last urgent care visit which she has been taking, had a normal bowel movement yesterday.  She states that she has had pneumonia in the past, no history of asthma or chronic obstructive pulmonary disease.  With the continued symptoms came to the urgent care for evaluation.  She states that there have been to other coworkers who have had exposure or have now tested positive for COVID-19.  Medical Decision Making:  59-year-old well-appearing female who presents to the urgent care with cough and nausea and vomiting over the past 2 weeks.  Reviewed patient's previous urgent care notes as well as immunization record.  Her vital signs are stable in the urgent care today and exam is largely benign.  Given her history and current complaints did obtain a chest x-ray which appears negative, formal interpretation was pending at time of discharge.  She was provided Zofran in the urgent care today which she did state helps with the nausea.  Discussed with patient that I do feel that COVID-19 testing should be collected as at the time of her symptoms and given her continued symptoms she has not had full immunity from the vaccination and this could still be a COVID-19 infection.  She is in agreeance and COVID testing is pending.  Prescribed refill of her Zofran as well as Tessalon for cough relief and advised continued symptomatic measures and close follow-up with PCP for any persistent symptoms.  She was provided a work note given her symptoms and COVID-19 testing she was provided the standard COVID-19 work letter.  Patient educated on warning signs and symptoms that would prompt immediate reevaluation. They conveyed understanding and were agreeable to this plan of care. All questions addressed at this time. Pt was non toxic appearing and not in any acute distress upon discharge.

Approximately three weeks after receiving Johnson & Johnson vaccine, I began to get pains in legs. Calves were aching and throbbing. Didn't think anything of it at first....just thought achy muscles and such. The day before Easter (April 3rd 2021) decided since the pain was continuing and the internet will scare you to death - I went to a local Emergency Room in advance,  I had an ultrasound on my left leg and it was noted I had DVT. (blood clot in left calf)  To briefly explain: I had an achilles issue back in Nov. 2020 (slight micro tear - achilles tendonitis) I thought maybe this was related to that, as I had not been to the doctor to get it checked until early March 2021. and it bothered me off and on for a few months. I thought the calf pain may have been related to that?  I explained to the emergency room doctor about my achilles and thought it was an issue related to that. They decided to perform an ultrasound on my left leg. Which noted the DVT/Blood Clot. They put me on a starter pack of Xarelto and I am to follow up with my normal doctor on April 22, 2021.

client complained of dizziness after receiving 1st dose Moderna Covid Vaccine (lot# 0421321A, Exp. 5/7/21). At 1415 client reported to EMT feeling dizzy. EMT performed first assessment and gave water. Vitals: blood pressure: 110/70, pulse 77, oxygen 96%. Client alert and oriented. Current medical conditions: HIV and diabetes. Medications: clonazepam, alprozolam, aprovasc, metroprolol, bictegravir, metformin, and aspirin. Informed client we would extend his observation period. Within 5 minutes client stated improvement. 1530 vitals: blood pressure: 130/80, pulse 76, oxygen 96%. Client stated feeling much better. Vitals 1440: blood pressure 140/90, pulse 68, oxygen 97%. Client stated symptoms had resolved. Client advised to consult with provider prior to receiving second dose. Client drove himself today, stated feeling fine to drive. Last set of vitals at 1448: blood pressure 138/84, pulse 82, oxygen 96%. Per client dizziness resolved. ER precautions given. Client left facility at 1450 with steady gait.

Within one minute of receiving the vaccine, I started having tightness in my chest. I took two benedryl and alerted one of the volunteers who directed me to the nurse's station. After about 15 minutes and my husband getting out of the car to go get the person staffing the nurse's station, the EMTs were called over. At this point, I was having trouble swallowing but my vitals were ok so they told me to sit and wait. About five minutes later, my tongue had swollen enough that I was having trouble swallowing my saliva. My husband called the EMTs back over and they gave me a shot of epinephrine. I declined the ambulance but did go directly to the nearest urgent care/ER where I was very quickly hooked up to an IV and given a dose of Pepcid intravenously.  About 2 hours later I started having trouble breathing again and was given a dose of Benedryl through the IV and a breathing treatment.  I was 'ok' but not feeling like the tightness in my chest and throat were all gone 2 hours after that, so I was given a does of steroids through the IV and released with directions to take zyrtec and ranitidine 2x a day for a few days.
LAB_DATA: Blood and urine samples were taken. I assume they came back normal? I was also given an EKG because my heart rate was all over the place. The EKG did come back normal.

6-7 hours after receiving, I got a headache, and became very tired & achey all over. I took ibuprofen & acetaminophen and felt reasonably better for a few hours. Then later that night (12-18 hours after vaccine) I became much sicker and was unable to sleep. I had a low fever, upset stomach, severe chills (couldn't stop shaking/shivering for over an hour) body aches, and an extremely bad headache. I continued to use ibuprofen and acetaminophen but even combined they weren't nearly enough to relieve my symptoms. Late into the night around 3-4am (15-16 hours after vaccine) nausea became the worst side effect, surpassing the headache. I eventually vomited around 4am, after which point the symptoms became more bearable and I managed to sleep a couple hours. Thursday/Friday (two days after vaccine) I still felt very weak, achey, and tired and had to call out of work both days. I was never again in the severe discomfort I experienced Wednesday night/Thursday morning, but I still felt a little tired, achey, and mildly sour stomach on days 3 &4 (Saturday/Sunday). Monday morning I felt similarly tired & achey, but I do feel essentially back to normal Monday night.

I'm not a medical professional, I'm reporting this due to the proximity in which the events occurred. I am a 33 year female with no history or family history of blood clots. I received the 2nd dose of my Pfizer vaccine on Apr 2 and on Apr 5 I began experiencing pain in my right leg. I had not injured it, and by Apr 14 I felt compelled due to the increased pain to contact a medical professional. They ran a d-dimer and mine came back high at 0.89. I was instructed by my PAC to go to the ER and tell them about the elevated d-dimer results. At the ER they performed an ultrasound and confirmed "Acute occlusive deep venous thrombosis in the right calf involving the entire length of 1 peroneal vein.". They also performed a CT scan on my chest and discovered "Right lower lobe distal segmental and subsegmental pulmonary artery emboli". They also performed a series of blood tests, all of those came back fine. I am being treated with 15mg of rivaroxaban (Xeralto).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received Moderna COVID vaccination 4/1/21. About 27 hours later, he felt muscle spasming across his chest. He then developed neck pain, tingling that goes into right and left arms/fingers. Was started on oral steroids by his PCP on 4/6/21. Given worsening symptoms and new development of urinary retention. Patient was admitted to Hospital 4/8-4/11. Suspected to have cervical transverse myelitis.  Re-admitted 4/12 due to worsening generalized weakness, significant numbness, gait/coordination issues, and several falls. Differential diagnosis includes guillain barre syndrome vs. transverse myelitis. No MS on brain MRI. No cord lesion. Treatment included IVIG 0.5g/kg daily x 4 days, B12, 1 mg IM daily x 3 days. bilateral neural foraminal stenosis at L5-S1.  4/7: MRI cervical spine: Small focal area of increased T2 signal within the central cervical cord at the C2 level without associated postcontrast enhancement. Within 15-20 minutes of receiving vaccine, I felt something in my chest. A slight pain or pang for a few seconds then it went away. The next day, I had noticeable visible swelling of my left breast and  lymph nodes under my left armpit even though injection was on rt arm. This was checked out by radiologist with a mammogram/ultrasound and lefts side looked fine, right side was suspicious of a legion which was biopsies and turned out to be fibrosis. Don?t know if there?s a connection to vaccine or not.  What was equally if not more concerning were the chest pains which returned a few more times getting stronger  that first week after the vaccine. It was a pulling sensation on the left side of my chest that, if 10x stronger, would feel (or be?) a heart attack. And that was after the 1st dose, so I am extremely hesitant to take the 2nd dose should those particular side effects intensify. I have googled it and can find no information about chest pains after the vaccine.  On a side note, my first cousin went into cardiac arrest after receiving his vaccination. He was dead and they brought him back. I?d like to avoid this.
LAB_DATA: As stated above, the results of my mammogram/ultrasound and biopsy were thankfully clear.   I have not consulted with a cardiologist yet.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Hi I was vaccinated Thursday April 8th 2021 at approximately 9:15am. I kept a log so I could share my experience with my friends and family. After vaccination I was fine for a few hours but I randomly got a case of  watery eyes that would last about 15 minutes and then clear up. This happened 4 times over a 9 hour period. Around 9 hours after vaccination I started to feel like I had a cold and my skin all over my body ached to touch and my heart started racing. I felt sunburned and nauseous and went to bed. 13 hours exactly after vaccination I was hit hard with intense chills to the point of teeth chattering and full body shivering. 15 hours after injection I woke up intensely hot and I had a massive headache, full body pain, a tickle deep in my lungs that made me cough, nausea, and a fever of 101. I also was having extreme heart palpitations. I have a laser thermometer and I discovered my fever was 101.5 at my forehead but my neck and chest were 103. I took ibuprofen and kept patting myself with cold wet wash cloths to combat the fever. At this point I debated going to the hospital. I had intense fatigue and I was too weak to move but too sick to sleep. This level of fever and symptoms went on for about a day and a half. Since my vaccination I am still fatigued, I get winded very easily, something small like feeding my dog makes me break out in a sweat, and I need to lay down. I am still weak and fatigued but not to the same level as before and it changes every day. I have a sore throat, headaches, occasionally my body will twitch in random places, fever will pop up and go away, I cough gag and get very weak under any physical stress. I did not have injection site pain out of the ordinary until 48 hours after injection and it felt like a shotgun blast to the arm.. I did have very unusual joint pain from the start. I was injected in my upper left arm, but my lower right ankle was painful and my left wrist...    I am a 38 year old male with treated hypertension, obesity and sleep apnea. My mother who is 65 was vaccinated at the same time as myself and her symptoms were slow onset and much milder than mine but she too has headaches, upset stomach, fatigue, watery eyes, fever, chills, twitches, injection pain, etc.
ALLERGIES: Penicillin, amoxicillin, erythromycin, ceftin, Lisinopril, metroprolo, amlodipine,

I drank 7-8 huge glasses of water & in the afternoon the color was light, but very smelly. The lower back pain still present, but I don't have fever right now. LAB_DATA: Because the water change the color of the urine, I didn't go to the ER as my doctor advised me.
CUR_ILL: none, but had been infected with Covid19 in Jan 17, 2021 was extremelly sick for 2 months.

I received the Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine EUA at roughly 2:15pm on Sunday 4/11/21. I waited at the vaccination site for 30 minutes and did not have any adverse effects. I went through the rest of my day without any adverse effects. I went to bed at 9:00pm. I woke up at 11:00pm with body aches and chills. I could not stop shivering. I then became very warm. I alternated between freezing/shivering and burning up all night. I felt very sore and my muscles hurt. It was primarily my upper body that hurt, not my lower body. My arms, torso, back, and neck hurt to move. I was very sensitive to everything I touched. It felt uncomfortable to touch the blankets in my bed or the water when I washed my hands. It did not hurt to do that, it just felt sensitive and uncomfortable. Around 5:00am I got a terrible headache. It felt like my head was made out of a lead ball. It hurt to move lift my head. My face hurt and felt like I had pressure. This lasted all day for Monday 4/12/21. After 5:00pm I slowly started to feel better. My body aches went away. I still had a headache, but it was far less severe. It is approximately 7:00am on 4/13/21 as I am filling this out. I still have a minor but persisting headache. My left arm is sore at the injection site. I am feeling much better than I was.

He ran tests and diagnosed me with branch retinal vein occlusion in my left eye. This is typically caused by a blood clot in the eye. The occlusion caused swelling in my retina and macula which caused my vision loss. I was treated with an injection of Eylea (anti-VEGF) to reduce the swelling on my retina/macula. I will need to have these injections every 4 weeks to maintain my sight.

Patient was administered covid vaccine (Moderna) at approximately 1025, at that time patient was recommended to sit in observation area for 15 minutes to monitor for reactions. At 1043 patient reported to clinic personnel that she was feeling tingling in her mouth. Nurse guided patient to a private area where patient could lay and be closely monitored. At that time patient reported having tingling in her mouth and a "metallic taste" but denied inability to swallow or shortness of breath. At 1044 nurse administered 25 mg of Benadryl orally to patient and educated her that she should remain in the facility for 30 minutes to monitor that her symptoms wouldn't worsen. At 1054 nurse reassess patient, patient reported that the tingling in her tongue had worsen slightly but denied difficulty swallowing or breathing. At 1104 nurse reassessed patient, patient denied any further advancement of symptoms and that she felt the same as last assessment. At 1113 patient reported that she noticed her swallowing had become more difficult and the tingling had spread to her throat, nurse also noticed that her voice pitch had changed. Nurse manager and supervisor were notified at this time. At 1118 Nurse administered a 0.5 mg dose of epinephrine to patient in her left deltoid and 911 was called. Nurse assessed vitals at this time heart rate was 117, oxygen saturation was at 97%, and her lung sounds were clear. At 1124 emergency personnel arrived and assessed patient, at that time they took over patients care. At 1126 EMS wheeled patient out of clinic on a stretched.

I received the vaccine on Wednesday, April 7th.  I was told I had an anaphylactic reaction at the time of injection: I started sweating upon receiving the vaccine, my blood pressure dropped, and I almost passed out. I was monitored for 30 mins before being sent home. Other than some fatigue, I was fine the rest of the day.  On Thursday, April 8th, I was tired but felt fine otherwise.  Friday and Saturday, April 9th and 10th, I felt like I was back to normal and even did some light exercise.  On Sunday morning, April 10th, the left side of my body (side of injection) went numb, I had extreme vertigo, shortness of breath, and blotches that appeared in random places. It didn't look like hives, but rather looked like strips of red. I didn't feel like I was having an allergic reaction, but something did not feel right. I consider myself a pretty healthy guy with a healthy lifestyle. I did not feel the need to go to the ER quite yet, but I did have a friend come over to monitor me.  My friend did some acupuncture which helped resolve the numbness and dizziness and some of the blotches, and also mentioned concerns regarding blood circulation and potential clotting issues she thought I was having.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Immediately after injection: pain and soreness around injection site.  Starting about 3-4 hours later: impaired coordination.  The next morning: severe dehydration, disorientation, loss of balance, very low energy, headache, body aches, inability to remain standing or sitting, difficulty walking, fever, feeling hot and cold, sweating and shivering intermittently and sometimes both at the same time, impaired mental focus, worsened pain and soreness around the injection site, nightmares. Slept the majority of the day, rising only to eat and drink lots of water.  Symptoms abated throughout the day. By about 7pm, I was able to sit up enough to play some video games.  The second morning: most symptoms gone or almost unnoticeable.  Hot/cold flashes, impaired coordination and low energy continue, but improving. Attempted to go out for my usual 2-mile jog after work, but only made it about one block walking before becoming both too cold and too tired to continue.  The third day, afternoon: completed my usual 2-mile route, at a walk, with frequent stops to rest.  No noticeable symptoms from the 4th day after injection, onwards.
ALLERGIES: Peppermint (mild - sneezing), Peanuts (mild - throat itching), Hazelnuts (airway constriction)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received first dose of COVID vaccine at 1:10pm without issue. During his 15 minute waiting period post vaccination, at approx 1:15pm, patient experienced a syncopal event, + for striking his head. He never lost vitals, and promptly woke up. at 1:22pm, his vitals were initially BP 90/42, HR 45, pulse ox 100% on room air, and RR 16. He complained of dizziness and blurred vision, but was AOX3 with all cranial nerves intact. 911 was called for patient to be assessed. Vitals were then checked again at 1:29 pm, BP 110/62, HR 62, pulse ox 100%, RR 16.  At this time, all of patient's symptoms had resolved. EMS arrived at 1:39pm and checked his BS which was 114. At this point patient no longer wanted to go to ER. EMS spoke with on call provider who gave verbal okey for patient to no go to the ER, but gave strict ER precautions such as headaches, vomitting, vision changes, etc. Patient was able to teach back. Patient reports that this (passing out) frequently occurs to him anytime he has to get shots or blood work done and he has seeked medical attention afterwards before with no resolution. Patient left at 1:46pm. He walked home.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The night of the shot I had a headache and some fatigue with some nausea. The next morning when I woke up around 8 am my arm was sore and my entire body felt achy. Over the next couple hours my body was progressively achy to the point of not wanting to move. By 12 pm I was in tears of just how much my body hurt. This is also around the time I had a fever of 101.3. I took a double dose of ibuprofen and attempted to sleep it off however I was only able to fade in and out of sleep because despite taking medicine my fever started to climb more and more high and the chills started to intensify. I recorded my fever through out the day and watched it climb more and more high until about 6 pm it was at 103.4. My head was pounding, my ears were hearting, my body aches so much and despite having chills I felt as if my body was over heating to the point where I had to put a bag of ice on my neck and a cool wash cloth on my head to cool down. I took more ibuprofen and eventually my fever went down again. By 11 pm it was back down to 101.3 and I felt so exhausted o went to bed however I woke up about every 2 hours and tossed and turned all night as my fever went back up to about 102 and I had chills. I woke up today about 7 am feeling better from yesterday but my body is still slightly achy, fever is low grade at 100.6 and the chills have eased. The sides in the back of my throat are very swollen and painful still though and have been since the night I received the shot.
CUR_ILL: No other Illnesses however 3 days after receiving my first vaccination in March I did have to receive a tetanus shot after getting an old rusty nail in my arm

SYMPTOM_TEXT: She had the vaccine, and it woke her up from a sound sleep feeling like she had been punched in the middle of her back as hard as they could.  Her rib cage, stomach muscles were so tight, her shoulders were breaking, feeling like everything was crushing inside of her, between her shoulder blades extremely and in the center of her back and she could not breath.  She literally had to talk herself into breathing pattern so she did not hyperventilate, and couched herself in the nose/out through the mouth for 3 hours, and did not want touched.   She went to sleep and when she woke up she felt heaviness in her chest, but could still feels like she has a target area in the center of her back, and still has this feeling if she takes a deep breath.   Then she had the body aches, a little bit of the cold chills, and the routine side effects.  She fell asleep that night, but when she woke up Saturday morning when she got undressed her entire stomach and back were red as if she had gotten sunburned.  Then about an hour and half after that it went to the inside of her arms with the redness, especially where the elbows bend.  She then went to and spoke with the pharmacist and got some Benadryl and the symptoms subsided except if she takes a deep breath/Inhale real deep can still feel where the area was on the back that was excruciating.  She called the doctor on Monday morning and they told her if she had any  more issues then to go to the ER.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt was noted to be sliding/falling our of chair to his right side. Patient appeared unresponsive. Pt was hoisted down to the floor (by this RN) and placed in Trendelenburg position. Pt?s eyes were noted to be open with some snoring respiration sounds. Pt?s facemask was removed. Pt then became arousable, confused about circumstances, and what had happened. Pt reports he believe he fell asleep in the chair. Pt was able to ambulate out of the facility without assistance after an appropriate amount of time. Patients vital signs were recorded during the event.
LAB_DATA: Other information to note. Patient vital signs were obtained in Trendelenburg position with a BP of 120/50, R-18, and P-93. Once patient stated he was feeling ok, he was assisted back to a sitting position, with a BP of 130/70, R-16, and P-120. Pt?s VS were repeated a few moments later, with a BP of 120/78, R-16, and P-95. Pt appeared frightened and very confused when he was waking up on the floor with no recollection of the events leading to him being on the floor. Pt appeared embarrassed and states he believed he fell asleep in the chair, however, clinically, I believe the patient had a syncopal event. The patient was about to fall completely out of his chair, and did not respond to be being lifted out of his chair and placed on the floor. It wasn?t until his legs were lifted above his head that he began to wake up rapidly with the above note. Patient?s skin condition and pallor was warm, dry, and intact during the entire event. No diaphoresis noted. Patient was monitored and was able to ambulate out of the facility unassisted after an appropriate amount of time.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient arrived to clinic to receive Janssen COVID-19 vaccine. Patient was accompanied by father. After consenting to receive vaccine, vaccine was given to left deltoid muscle. After about eight minutes, patient started to express feeling strange, reporting that she felt like she was going to pass out. Patient became clammy and pale. Clinic MD was called for assistance. Patient was assessed by paramedics, EKG done and was NSR, blood glucose done, and VS several times throughout incident. Patient was initially hypotensive with BP 80s/60s, with BP returning to 116/62 within a few minutes. Patient was taken home by parents following incident, electing not to go to hospital with paramedics. Patient was in good condition when leaving clinic with directions from clinic staff and paramedics to seek emergent care if needed.

I went back to bed and slept all through the night.  This morning (4/13/2021--2 days after injection) I feel much better--only have some slight chills and arm soreness. I received my 2nd dose of Moderna at 12:20 on 4/8/21. Starting at 11:30 p.m. that same day, I began to have severe chills, followed by fever in 101-102 degree range and full body aches. Fever and aches continued until I began to treat with Extra-Strength Tylenol at 9:00 AM on 4/9/21, which helped to ameliorate symptoms, although temperature stayed above normal and both aches returned as soon as Tylenol wore off.  I continued to use maximum dose of Tylenol through that day (3000 mg over 24 hours).  By the morning of 4/10, I had mild fever (100 - 101 degrees) and a persistent headache, but no more body aches.  I continued to treat with Tylenol through that day.  By 10 p.m. on 4/10, my symptoms had all resolved.   I should note that I would have begun treatment with Tylenol sooner, but I had seen conflicting information about whether Tylenol use after the vaccine injection would inhibit the immune response.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Immediately when I received the injection, I felt a cool fluid rush around my heart with a moderate discomfort/pain. I reported this to the tech who administered. He didn't seem alarmed & advised I wait 15 mins. I still felt a "coolness" around my chest but otherwise felt "fine" so I was permitted to leave. As the day went on, I felt my chest (lungs & area around my heart) feel tighter & tighter & my breath grew more & more "shallow" like I couldn't take deep enough breaths & I was short of breath. In the evening, it intensified. I was very fatigued (couldn't go up our stairs or talk in complete sentences without feeling "winded"). The tightness in my chest was worse & was accompanied by periodic acute pain in my heart. I also had pain my lower back. I went to the emergency room around 10PM that night. An EKG, blood tests & chest X-ray were conducted. The ER doctor said all tests came back "normal" & they weren't sure what my issue was. I went home & rested. I woke the next morning with the acute pains gone but the tightness still lingered. I did not feel "normal" until almost 72 hours after my vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Around 8am in the morning, I got a intramuscular shot in my left arm on/around the deltoid muscle. I stayed at the vaccine administration location for about 30 minutes to ensure I felt okay, and left. Around 8:45 am I noticed the left side of my face was going numb. By 9am, a 2" radius around my rear molars was completely numb. I immediately called the doctor who oversaw the administration and began constant communication with the doctor. I did not loose any functionality of muscles, my ability to talk, eat, or breathe. I simply felt like I had a very strong novacane shot to the upper rear gum and that numbness radiated out.  Under regular communications with the doctor and his team, I did daily check ins and updates with how I felt. The numbness started to wear off after 10 days of no medical intervention. 13 days post injection was the last day I felt any numbness. 14 days after injection I felt fine. I have not gotten the second shot. I have not felt any side effects since then.

My vision started blurring, as well, eventually going completely black. For a solid 5-10 seconds, I could neither hear clearly nor see at all. I was conscious, because I could think relatively clearly, and I could feel my eyes blinking and could wiggle my fingers, but that was it. Once the episode passed, I immediately sat down. About a minute later, I started having excruciating abdominal pain. The pain was wracking my whole body, causing me to go pale (as I later saw once I could hobble to the bathroom) and making me sweat. After about twenty minutes, the whole thing passed and I was left with minor dizziness and slight nausea. Now, three days later, I still have some of the dizziness, but none of the blindness, deafness, or pain has returned. All other side effects, such as soreness, have completely left.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt received her vaccine in her L deltoid at 3:26PM 04/10/2021. At 3:38PM, the Pt alerted Observers that she felt dizzy and warm. Pt was assisted to one of the cots for assessment. Vitals at 3:40 (138/88BP, 126P, 32RR, 97%). PT's skin was warm, dry, and of normal color. Pt's skin turgor was normal. When assessed, the Pt's tongue was moist and did not appear cracked, therefore, poor hydration was not a differential diagnosis. Pt stated she had only had a candy snack approximately 2 hours prior to the incident. Secondary to this information and the Pt's complaints, the Observer deduced a low BGL was the cause of the Pt's symptoms. Pt was given 15g of oral glucose, and self administered 350ml water orally. (Cont. Pg 2)    A Glucometer was not available, so Pt's BGL was not able to be assessed. VS at 3:50(136/78, 80P, 18R, 100%) Pt stated feeling improved.  Pt stated she did not want any further EMS assistance or to be transported to the ED.  Pt was assisted outside of the facility by Observer. **All care occurred without complications.** **All times are approximate secondary to Pt care being paramount**

Patient denies any history of any vaccine reactions in the past, to penicillin and seasonal allergies otherwise denies any sensitivities.  Denies any history of autoimmune diseases.   Patient denies any HA, dizziness, vision changes, chest pain, shortness of breath, abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, fevers chills, dysuria. Since that date (4/6/21 3am), I have experienced a headache like never before. 4/7 and 4/11 were the worst headaches I?ve ever had in my life. I was hysterically crying with ice packs on my head in the dark, as light was very bothersome. Taking Tylenol every 4 hrs during daytime while awake barely shook this headache. I had a good day on 4/10, but then had the set back with the worst headache ever on 4/11. I spoke with my doctor?s office on 4/7 and they decided I most likely had a concussion and could recover at home. I called again 4/12 in the AM after having the worst headache of my life on 4/11 and they could not get me in for a visit until 4/13. I just left that appointment and while I passed their ?neuro? physical exam, I am still experiencing these headaches along with dizziness and shortness of breath when doing the smallest task or bending down and getting back up. I?ve requested a CT Scan to ensure there isn?t a brain bleed causing these issues from my fall which occurred due to the dizziness from receiving this Covid vaccine.

36 y.o. female referred for the above chief complaint.   She has no significant medical history and presented with a headache that became severe 3 days ago.  She received the Johnson and Johnson COVID vaccine on March 25th and had a mild headache following that which she attributed to the vaccine.  3 days ago the pain became excruciating and was associated with vomiting.  This prompted presentation to the ED where she was treated with Dilaudid. She was discharged home and has been using her mom's headache cocktail with some transient relief.  She presented back to the ED today with continued symptoms.  MRV revealed a venous sinus thrombosis and neurology was therefore consulted.   She has no history of clots personally or in the family.  Her dad did have a stroke in his 50s.  Patient otherwise denies any other associated speech change, vision change, extremity numbness, extremity weakness, coordination difficulty, or dizziness. Patient admitted to the neurology ICU and started on anticoagulation.

A patient presenting to hospital OB department received Moderna doses on 1/20/21 and 2/18/21.  She received them from health department at a clinic.  She self-quarantined from 3/15 to 3/31 due to approaching her delivery date.  She was in contact with 2 friends on 3/10 which both tested positive on the 22nd and 26th respectively.   She presented to OB initially on 4/1 for labor & delivery.  She was found to be COVID positive at this time after being COVID tested - she had no prior symptons of COVID.   She had to have an unscheduled c-section after 24 hours in labor.  While laboring she did go into a critical blood pressure range.  She was treated appropriately with medication.  Patient did well postpartum and postop.  Lungs were clear and patient afebrile.  Patient discharged 4/4.    Patient returned to hospital on 4/6 for elevated blood pressure (was advised on previous discharge to monitor blood pressures at home and to report if elevated).  Her inpatient stay involved being treated for elevated blood pressure with magnesium sulfate, nifedipine, and labetalol.  She had swelling in lower extremities and has had a Doppler study which showed no DVT.  She was on a blood thinner enoxaparin though because of postop status and also COVID.  She went home on 4/10 advised to follow up with provider if any more issues were to arise.  She went home on enoxaparin 40mg subcutaneous for 10 days, nifedipine ER 60mg daily, and labetalol 400mg three times daily.  Blood pressure elevation probably related to course of L&D case but reporting due to the fact that patient had received both doses of the COVID vaccine and had tested positive during the course of the L&D.

March 5, 2021: 1st dose of Pfizer vaccine. Severe site pain.  March 23, 2021: 2nd dose of Pfizer vaccine. Felt very restless and sick during night, by the next morning symptoms really sat in.  March 24, 2021: Went to Urgent Care due to fever. Had COVID-19 test (negative). Very close to passing out there (put head between knees and did not). Was sent to emergency room immediately due to heart rate (high 140s-150s. Highest known was 152 BPM). ER performed following: portable chest x-ray, blood tests, urine tests, EKG. Was told results were all normal with the exception of EKG (not told anything about it, form listed as abnormal). Passed out 2x at hospital. Was given one IV rehydration solution and released that night. Symptoms below lasted for several days: Headache Aches Nausea Aggressive shakes Shortness of breath Confusion Dizziness Site pain (also developed bump under arm) Fever - 103.8 (after 2 Advil, 2 Tylenol, 3 ice packs and eating frozen grapes) Heavy sweats Racing heart Restless  March 30, 2021: Still having frequent heart palpitations (they come and go but happen several times during the day. Keep having very high heart rates). Went to doctor. While there, nurse noted irregular heartbeat that sounded like it was ?skipping a beat? and heart rate was also jumping all over the place (high pace, low pace, high, etc.). It was clear something was abnormal. Doctor gave EKG approximately 20 minutes later, EKG looked normal. Was told to come back next morning for blood work and to cut out caffeine.  March 31, 2021: Came in for blood work to check thyroid.  April 6, 2021: Thyroid results were normal. Still having palpitations among other symptoms (see April 12 for more info) so was told to come in. Was given ?work from home? note and referred to cardiologist.  April 12, 2021: Appointment at cardiologist. Still having severe palpitations, occasional dizziness/ lightheadedness, nausea, shortness of breath, exhaustion and chest pain. Heart rate was recorded this day to have gotten up to 139 BPM-- was very high majority of the day. EKG was normal (with exception of high heart rate) but 30 mins later doctor observed high heart rate and abnormal rhythm. Was told to come back in a week and one day for a heart ultrasound and heart monitoring for three days. Still no caffeine intake since 3/30/21. Previous heart rates taken at doctor's visits over the years for comparison below. Never had any prior heart problems whatsoever:  8/29/18: 70 BPM 9/17/18: 88 BPM 10/17/18: 64 BPM 10/31/18: 73 BPM 1/21/19: 78 BPM Note: At this point, I have missed over a  week and a half of work, and worked from home for over a week. I'm not any better heart wise at all over the course of three weeks post vaccine.
LAB_DATA: Three EKGs, two blood tests, urine tests, portable X-ray, heart ultrasound, heart monitoring (see above item 18 for more information and dates).
HISTORY: No prior medical history except migraines (no medications taken for them)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woke up between 10:30 and 11pm night of vaccine administration with full body shaking and shortness of breath. It?s unclear if shortness of breath was a direct result of the severity or the shaking or something else underlying the shakes. Walking or standing for any period of time was nearly impossible. I felt too warm and too cold at the same time and felt myself sweating but also shivering. My temperature was 99.6 (high for me - I?m usually low, around 96-97 on average) which persisted until around 5:30-6am the following morning. A severely painful, throbbing headache was present until well into the next evening. The symptoms of the headache did subside with use of OTC extra strength Tylenol (2 oral every 6 hours, taken twice totally 4 over the course of 24 hrs) but the headache was still felt somewhat even with use of Tylenol. Moderate fatigue was present all of 4/9 and until around mid morning of 4/10. Pain at the injection site was present but only noticed if laying on the affected arm (left) or if the site was accidentally touched. Dull aching at the site was felt on occasion until the following Monday, 4/12. All other symptoms had fully subsided by 4/10. As of today, 4/13, I am symptom free but I have noticed that I am taking deep breaths every once in a while (maybe several times an hour) as if I?m trying to catch my breath/I can?t catch a full satisfying breath. It feels somewhat like breathing through a straw for a few moments and I breath in until a full breath ?catchs?.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within the first 5 minutes after the vaccination, I felt faint, lightheaded, dizzy, disillusioned, like I had vertigo also. I experienced these symptoms w/in the first 5 minutes once I left the designated vaccination area. My entire body felt hot, my face was red, I felt sweaty. I went to find a nurse nearby who walked me to an area to sit/rest so that she could monitor me. I did inform her that I had my EpiPen with me, however, she recommended that if I had Benadryl to take it immediately. She provided me w/water and I took one 25mg pill. She continuously took my pulse as I felt my heartbeat was fast, I had anxiety about the way I was feeling because I felt short of breath. While my throat/chest did not feel tight, I did feel a heaviness in my chest and my breathing was somewhat labored. My face became flushed and then pale/drained and I began to feel extremely nauseous w/in 10 minutes. The nurse continued to monitor/take my pulse/heart rate at this time. I did experience stomach cramps and had to go to the bathroom. I experienced diarrhea and continued to feel nauseous while in the bathroom. I continued to feel dizzy and just out of sorts so I was asked to remain at the hospital. I was asked if I'd like to be taken to the ER, however, I chose not to go to the emergency room because I did not want to incur any additional hospital charges if they were not going to utilize my EpiPen. I remained at Hospital vaccination clinic at the hospital for what I believe was approximately 2.5 hours. I did ultimately eat a small bag of pretzels and drank a small bottle of water. Thankfully, the Benadryl did help fairly quickly and tremendously to get me over the hump of symptoms and anxiety that I was feeling. Once I returned home, I literally just collapsed in bed and remained there basically sleeping for over the course of the next 48 hours. I followed a diet as my stomach was still upset. I did have a slight fever, but it did not get any higher than 99-100. I felt clammy the first day/evening, with subsequent chills, but ultimately, by Friday night and into Saturday, I felt well enough to get out of bed and move around the house. I felt back to some normalcy on Sunday. My left arm was swollen from Wednesday (day of vaccination) to Saturday.  I could not lift my arm, or sleep on my left side due to the pain and I also couldn't lift my arm for approximately 48 hours.
OTHER_MEDS: BuPROPion Hydrochloride XL 150 mg/24 hours oral tablet, extended release
ALLERGIES: Penicillin, Sulfa, Erythromycin, Augmentin, Phenergan, Ativan, Topamax, Mastocol, Bee Allergy, Seasonal Allergies - These are a few of my drug allergies, however, I cannot remember all of them at this particular time unfortunately. I can research my records further and provide a separate list if needed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received the vaccine at 12 on April 10th. Woke up at 2am with high fever (sorry, never actually took my body temp), chills, uncontrollable body shakes, body aches and extreme nausea. Went back to sleep around 5am. Woke up around 10am on April 11th with 99.9 body temp. Took more acetaminophen and ibuprofen to control the body aches and fever. Spent the day in bed on April 11th, with very little appetite and flu like symptoms. Gotten progressively better throughout the day but never felt quite right. On April 12th, was still feeling tired and had some muscle aches but was overall feeling much better. Noticed the lymph nodes under my left armpit (I received the vaccine in the left arm) were quite tender to the touch. Was able to resume normal activities but didn't feel like I was quite ready to go to the gym. On April 13th, feeling normal, finally, aside from the tenderness of the lymph nodes (left armpit).

I would like to report what happened with all the facts.  One week after I had vaccine, I had very serious nose bleeding in the morning. I said very serious because I felt it cannot stop by itself. I called 911 and went to ER. First time, I use 911 and ER. All previous nose bleeding is very minor and it will stop in a minute. But this time, I just felt the blood just pouring into my mouth. So I was scared and  asked my wife called 911. After 2-3 hours, the bleeding stopped and I back home. To be cautious, I made an appointment with family doctor on next day (24th). But the bleeding happened again in the evening ( cannot remember exactly, but around 9pm). This time I just used the clipper for my nose and it took another 2 hours for the bleeding to stop. I had a very rough night while sitting on bed and had very little sleep. The next morning (24th), the bleeding come back after I used the restroom. The same feeling as the two bleeding before. I rushed to doctor's office even not my appointment yet. The family doctor said he cannot do anything since he cannot observe the place of blooding and he does not have instrument needed. I was referred to a specialist. And luckily I had the same day appointment. We rushed there and after roughly several hours waiting, I was the specialist and finally he did the treatment. Since then, my nose is ok and no serious bleeding again.  After I saw the side effects of JJ vaccine, I think it is better for me to report you what happened. I strongly suspect that my serious bleeding was caused by the drop of platelet which was side effect of the vaccine. I will have one blood work today. And will let you know results if you are interested. Again, I never had such serious bleeding before and that is the reason for my suspect.  All the best

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 10 days after the vaccine I developed dizziness, tachycardia, dry mouth,chest pressure, shortness of breath and felt like I was going to pass out, and I had a feeling of extreme doom. I was transported to a clinic. There I had a heart rate of 140 with irregular beats. Continued feeling of doom. An EKG showed ST depression. Symptoms improved with nitroglycerin. The clinic didn't have the technology to provide care so I was emergently transported again. At that hospital my D-dimer was positive and that lead to a CT Angiogram. This showed a pulmonary embolism. Doppler studies of both legs were negative. I was placed on Heparin for several hours and then switched to Eliquis. About 6 hours after being on Eliquis I had the exact same original symptoms and again nitro was given which helped the symptoms. I was placed back on Heparin for a longer period of time. Once I was anticoagulated I was then switch to Eliquis 10mg BID for 7 days then 5mg BID for 6-9 months. I had a CT Angiogram of the head and neck which was normal. At this time I still have dizziness with standing and intermittently with sitting, extreme fatigue, shortness of breath.
LAB_DATA: April 7th, 2021 CTA of lungs showed pulmonary embolism in right lung April 7th, 2021 EKG tachycardia with ST depression April 8th, 2021 pelvic US- normal April 8th, 2021 Heart Echo- normal April 8th, 2021 CTA of head and neck-normal

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 4/5/21, two days after my second injection, I was sitting at my desk working (at home) when I noticed my vision wasn't clear even with my glasses on. I had been feeling nauseous for a few hours and then my eyes started bouncing back and forth uncontrollably. I was unable to see correctly or move from my chair. Once my eyes stopped moving my vision became tunnel vision and everything around it became foggy. I felt weak and dizzy. I started getting a headache. I didn't think I could even call out for help as I was unsure my voice would work. Once it all calmed down I figured it must be part of a migraine, even though nothing this extreme had ever happened before. I moved to my bed as I was suddenly completely exhausted, and immediately fell asleep for almost 3 hours. Once I got up I was still very groggy and had to force myself my. I stayed up for about 3 hours and went back to bed for the night. The next morning I woke and was feeling better so I figured it must have been a migraine. However a few hours later the same problems started back up again. I was having a hard time seeing my computer screen, I had a foggy head and was finding it hard to concentrate and do work. My headache started again and my vision started as foggy and became tunnel vision again. This time my eyes did not bounce, but my lips started tingling. This lasted for about 1 minute. This time with everything I was making sure to take a mental note of everything going on because I was scared I was going to have to call 911. Because I was home alone I opened my phone to dial if it got any worse. The event backed off enough that I took myself to the ER. By the time I was in the waiting room my head felt like a balloon and my whole body just felt "off." I can't explain how it felt, it just didn't feel normal. My headache never got overly severe like it does with a migraine, but I was worried about a stroke. The ER did a CT scan and did rule out a stroke, but was unsure of what it exactly what it was, but guessed it was an abnormal migraine attack and told me to follow up with my PCM in a couple of days and to keep my appointment with my neurologist on April 15th. The symptoms lasted a full week off and on every day, with a tampering down of severity of symptoms.

ALLERGIES: Topamax (full body rash) Singular (full body rash)

There were no side effects with the 1st dose.  The 2nd dose resulted in the following:   4 hrs in:  2 hives on thigh 12 hrs in:  More hives/welts on torso, feet, knees, elbows, hands, face, thighs 24 hrs in:  fever, chills, body aches (expected) and extensive amount of welts, hives all over the body and  swollen hands/feet, wrists/ankles to include itching and pain. The 2nd dose has triggered my Chronic Urticaria, which I first got in 2019 from what I believe was an ingredient in sunscreen (octinoxate).  At that time it took me 1 long year to completely get rid of those hives and that was successful by using a series of prednisone (which was damaging to my system and hard to get off of) and then finally Xolair.  I have not been off of the Xolair for even a year at this point and now, I am back to where I started.   I believe that the PEGs in the Pfizer vaccine has activated my urticaria.  I am now suffering with severe welts/hives and swollen hands.  Prednisone is not an option due to it mixing with the vaccine and I managed to get a low dose of Xolair yesterday (4/12/21) but that shot is slow-absorbing and I might not see relief for 7-8 days.  Additionally, my blood pressure was 160/100, which is consistent with presence of these welts/hives.  This includes a rapid heart beat as well. Had I known this was a even a remote possibility, I would not have received the Pfizer vaccine.  Chronic Hives is a life-altering issue as I have used a lot of sick time and missed events due to discomfort and swollen eyelids.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Thursday 04/08/21 - 1:35 PM Went to Fairgrounds to get the Johnson & Johnson - Janssen COVID-19 vaccine shot with my husband. Both of us wore our masks, walked in together, went through the line together, we both got the shot in our left arms and then set together and waited the 15 minutes before we could leave. A little later at home we were working on some landscape lighting and I felt a bit foggy, light headed and kind of out of it. I was drilling into masonry and the first hole went fine but the second one for some reason just wasn?t going and I touched the drill bit with my fingertip on my left hand to see if it had smoothed out and I knew in my head not to do it and that it should be hot as heck but I didn?t feel anything at all so later that evening when I took a shower my finger was burning and I knew I had burnt it. That evening I begin to feel crippling cold, my fingernail and toenail beds had turned purple and I was shivering violently. I got under a pile of blankets with my dog and  tried to slow my breathing I could feel my heart beating in my chest and it felt like the air I was breathing was cold and frosty. I had a 104+ fever that night. My husband got me some aspirin a cold washcloth for my head a popsicle and water to help bring down the fever. And I was able to sleep on and off that night. When I woke up I had a 103+ fever and a tingling and numbness in my arms. Before the fever my arms felt tight and cold and I had a tingle that ran from my elbows to my fingertips. Again it was aspirin cold washcloth and lots of water to drink to try and get my fever down.   Friday 04/09/21 Was spent in bed trying to drink water and sleep through it. My arm was sore, not at the injection site but the whole top part of my arm felt like I had been hit by a truck. I had a fever again that evening.   Saturday 04/10/21 I thankfully woke up fever free but my arms were tingling. I had to take my husband to the airport that morning at 6:30 AM. I came back home and went back to bed until about nine when I woke up my arms were cold and sore and tingling it seemed to be getting worse in my left arm and I felt shots of electricity from my elbow down to my fingertips. At one point I took a picture because my left arm hurt so much more than the right and my fingertip beds were purple on my left and pink on my right. I took aspirin and took a nap. I couldn?t hold my phone with both hands hands like normal sitting in bed because my left hand goes cold and achy. Woke up worried that both my arms were aching and tingling from my elbows to my fingertips seems to be where it stays the most. Then that pain subsided and my lip started to tingle. After a few hours that stopped but the tingling in my arms is about constant not as strong sometimes, not in both arms sometimes, it seems to almost always be in my left arm and at one point scary enough that I almost went to the ER. Went to bed around 11:30 PM and the tips of the toes on my left side were tingling and it went to the whole leg.  Sunday 04/12/21 I woke up with a coughing fit  and mucus at around 1:00AM and my right leg with a little tingly at 4:24 AM awake again and coughing woke me had to get a drink and my stomach was buzzing and stopped now just back to the bottom half of my left leg. All of a sudden after a coughing and sneezing fit I got a tremendously sore burning throat out of no where that only lasted about five minutes. I noticed my left arm straining to hold up the pizza box tonight when my right arm had no trouble at all. Then a little later in the day stiffness in the back of my neck. It is a weird strong dry cough and I was scared to go to the ER because my symptoms were so varied and ever-changing I didn?t know what they would do with me and I didn?t want to just get stuck in there for days with him not knowing or making it worse. I told my husband ? It?s so random I?m a little scared no one is going to know what to do with me...?I?ve had issues with allergic reactions and no one being able to diagnose them and me having to figure it out on my own on the Internet that I had Thyroid problems and that I was allergic to the sun for a few years in the past and aloe vera... I didn?t wanna wind up going, them not fixing anything and having a huge bill to pay. But this whole time my body is buzzing and tingling and going through something strange. At this point I am just telling my family I?m okay and what random symptoms I have had since we spoke last. They are on standby to watch my children if I need to go to the ER. The constant buzzing, numbness, cold tingling in my arms is worrisome.   Monday 04/12/21 I am use to the numbness and tingling being a constant thing on some part of my body... There are times when I feel fine but I know it won?t last long. We can add an upset stomach and diarrhea to the list. I had a metal taste in my mouth for a little bit today. Both arms legs and my lips have randomly buzzed, ached or tingled. The websites say call 911 for emergency or call your local medical provider for assistance so I called the local ER to see if they could tell me if my symptoms were normal or if it?s something I should come in for and they couldn?t give me any advice... I was told if you feel like you should come in then come in. I had a very strong sharp pain at my elbow of my right arm tonight that made me sit up in bed...   Tuesday 4/13/21 My left arm is still sore if people touch me or if I try to sleep on my side like I normally do it hurts trying to hold my phone with both hands my arm still goes cold and achy. So far this morning my arms are both tingling and my left leg and my lips so at this point I just say I?m buzzy. 11:25 AM randomly my right arm decided to feel worse for a change but is back to a low buzz... after a few minutes. I find myself holding them up or lifting them when they hurt it seems to help a little to elevate my arms to my chest. I am just waiting to see what comes out in the media, or to see if this gets any better, or if they learn what to do about it... It isnt over, it hasnt stopped yet.
ALLERGIES: Aloe Vera, Latex, Bees and Polymorphic Light Eruption in the past...

On 3/23, I received the vaccine. Within a few hours, my right elbow began to hurt and swell. On 3/24, I could not move my arm due to inflammation and intense pain. The skin was hot to touch. I also had a high fever and severe headache. (The fever broke within 24 hours and the headache lingered for about 48 hours.) On 3/25, the arm swelling started to decrease but was still intensely painful, red, and hot. I treated the arm with ice packs, Advil, and Bio-freeze. On 3/25, I also contacted my PCP by email with my concerns and progression photos of my arm. Another doc responded by having his nurse call me. They denied the reaction could be vaccine related. The nurse insisted on their diagnosis and that I should take antibiotics for a skin infection. I disagree because my symptoms did not match their explanation. On 3/31, I contacted my rheumatologist (due to the inflammation) and they referred me back to my PCP. I am filing this report b/c I believe this was related to the vaccine. Lesser symptoms remain.

On 4/9/21 an MRI of the brain was done with results finding no acute infarc and large area of increased C2 signal and cystic encephalomalacia in the left middle cerebral artery consistent with old infarct.  Provider felt something aggravated the old infarct in the patient's brain.  In lab results, reversed differential was noted indicating a viral process may be the cause.  Patient had previous treatment for Hep C which was cured.  It was thought the recent COVID vaccine may have contributed.  New onset diabetes was also noted and patient was started on medication.  facility MD believes the stroke like symptoms are more likely related to uncontrolled diabetes and not the COVID vaccine. SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 03/18, I started experiencing burning on my tongue. My tongue became swollen and more irritated throughout the day. This progressed in to 03/19, when my throat became sore and swollen as well. I felt like I do when I have strep throat with the amount of irritation in my  throat and tongue. By the evening of 03/19, my tongue was so swollen it was hard to talk and articulate sounds. It was difficult to swallow liquids and I started to get scared. I took a Benedryl and went to sleep. The irritation and swelling eased Saturday and by Sunday afternoon, it was like nothing happened. I went to my general practitioner who sent me to an allergist and everyone agrees it sounds like an anaphylactic response to the vaccine, though unusual in the timing. I still have some burning and irritation on my tongue. My allergist is doing testing and ordered me an Epi-Pen.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At 11:08 patient slumped down in chair and stated "oh no, here it goes." Patient lost consciousness at 11:09am.  I continued to speak to him and he was unable to hear initially.  He did cry out and gasp and tighten then started to have a few slow jerky movements bringing both arms and body up from the chair. It appeared as if he may vomit and I repositioned to ensure he would not slide off of the chair.  The movements lasted about a minute and then he started to come to.  He described feeling dizzy, disoriented, nauseous, and sweaty.  During the event his pupils were non responsive. At 11:17 he went pale and started feeling as if he was spinning and experiencing tingling.  He was still reclined in the chair and sitting up aided with the tingling.  He was given a cold pack to help regulate and given ice water at 11:18.  He stated he had not eaten yet today as he usually doesn't eat until 11. His temperature had dropped to 96.1 vs 97.5 prior to the vaccination.  BP was checked at 11:25 and was 120/72 which is lower than usual for him and to be expected with the LOC.  After drinking his water, I had him attempt to stand while grasping the wall/table for 2 minutes to assess his steadiness, then standing unassisted for 2 minutes.  After he felt steady enough we had him walk 10-15 feet and stand for another 2 minutes.  Patient was feeling tired and instructed not to drive home.  The situation was conveyed to his wife and they were instructed to seek ER/Urgent care if any of his symptoms reappeared. They stayed in the area to eat lunch and I checked in again at 12:12pm with the patient and he is feeling better after eating but still tired.  I also recommended following up with his primary as I will be sending her a copy of this report.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received her 1st dose COVID vaccine, Moderna, at 11:02AM, she was waiting in the waiting area. She became dizzy and light headed. While the pharmacy team was reaching to her chair, the patient's husband laid her on the floor.  (Pharmacy Manager) got to the patient 's side. She was awake, aware of her surrounding. I (staff pharmacist, administered the vaccine)  checked Pt's blood pressure, reading was 173/99. I gave few minutes to breath, rechecked her blood pressure in 2 minutes, it dropped down to159/82. Then rechecked it third time was 131/76. Patient was feeling fine, we gave her water and sat her on the chair. I checked her blood pressure again, reading was 117/66. Patient reported that she did not have breakfast, she ate a piece of candy, in 5 minute she stated that she feels just fine. Her husband reported that this is the fifth time she has this (unrelated to prior vaccinations). She doesn't have a PCP and has never checked for her previous events. Patient said she does not have a statement to write, she decided to leave the pharmacy area after assuring she feels normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On December 21st I got my first Pfizer Injection.  Had minimal side effects, that included a weird headache (I have migraines and this was unlike any migraine I ever had), it was like a halo above my ears and around the crown of my head.  I also had a sore arm.  No other issues.  On January 11th I got my second dose.  Again sore arm, nothing terrible.  This time I was prepared and over hydrated to prevent the headaches.  On day 2 after my shot I noticed both my shoulders starting to hurt and complained to my best friend I felt like a bus ran me over.  I said maybe it?s the shot but we shuffled it off to I slept funny.  2 weeks went by, same thing still going on; except some days my shoulders hurt so bad I couldn?t take my clothes off.  About 4 weeks post injection my knees also started to hurt.  I visit my chiropractor every 2-3 weeks regularly since having my daughter 12 years ago because my pelvis rotates out of place; her and I discussed what was going on and she said she had a couple other patients complain of similar things and it typically gets better after 6 weeks.  So I give it a few more days, decide to message my family care doctor just to let her know what?s going on.  She checks me for Rheumatoid Arthritis- that?s negative.  Checked my CRP-  which were elevated to basically say I was having an inflammatory response.  (I knew all these things already lol you don?t just wake up at 38 with RA with no family history but whatever).  Another week went by and I am at work and can?t stand up to walk- like crying in pain my knees and arms hurt so bad.  One of the anesthesiologist gives me a Decadron injection.  An hour later it was like magic, I actually had relief.  Unfortunately less than 48 hrs later the pain came back.  I went to my family doctor and had a conversation about all of this.  They put me on a tapering dose of Prednisone for 10 days- because unfortunately the max dose for Decadron is 6 days we decided to do Prednisone so I could have more days.  I started with 100 mg a day of Prednisone and tapered it down for 10 days.  I finally felt back to normal and it was amazing!!  Then 5 days after the last dose of Prednisone the pain came back yet again in my knees.  It hasn?t come back as bad in my shoulders but it?s definitely worse in my knees.  My family doctors recommendation is for me to see a rheumatologist; which I am waiting on an appointment for now.
LAB_DATA: CRP 2.2 on 2-12 Rheumatoid Factor Normal 2-12 CBC Diff- Eosinophils 0.58 on  2-12
OTHER_MEDS: Topamax ER- Fomotidine 40 mg- Singulair 10 mg
HISTORY: Shingles in 8/2020 Seasonal Allergy induced Asthma Seasonal Allergies

Patient was given juice and water and assisted to a quiet area to lay down. EMS stayed with her and continued to monitor.  After 30 minutes patient reported feeling better and left vaccine area with her friend.  She was feeling better by her report in the afternoon.  Received a call at 9:30pm that evening.  Reported same symptoms she had initially.  She was advised to go to the ER for further evaluation but she declined.  She took benadryl 25mg and rested.  Reported feeling better the next day.
